article.headline: Minnesota 90, N. Dakota St. 76
article.story: MINNEAPOLIS -- Senior Jamal Abu-Shamala scored nine of his season-high 20 points during a 14-1 run to start the game and Minnesota never trailed in a 90-76 victory over North Dakota State on Saturday. Lawrence Westbrook returned from a one-game absence due to an injured right shin to score 17 points for Minnesota. Ralph Sampson III had a season-high 12 points and Damian Johnson added 11. Minnesota (6-0) is off to its best start since racing out to the same record during the 1999-2000 season. Bison senior Mike Nelson paced North Dakota State (2-2) with a season-high 22 points. Ben Woodside and Brett Winkelman each added 16. The only other time Abu-Shamala had at least 20 points was when he scored a career-high 27 against Michigan in 2007. Minnesota improved to 24-1 all time against North Dakota State, with the Gophers' only loss to the Bison coming in 1936.
